-- The duplex canon has teeth: `aliceToBob` is performed by Alice (the first
-- actor, by the SVO subject-first canon), so Bob may not bear it. Constructing
-- the message the other way round (Bob first) is how Bob would become the
-- performer — see ok/regulative-actor-duplex.l4.

DECLARE Actor IS ONE OF Alice, Bob

DECLARE SendMessage HAS
  from IS AN Actor
  to   IS AN Actor
  body IS A STRING

aliceToBob MEANS SendMessage OF Alice, Bob, "hi"

GIVETH DEONTIC Actor SendMessage
wrong MEANS PARTY Bob MUST aliceToBob WITHIN 10   -- performed by Alice, not by Bob
